text:
You can upload them remotely. The process (roughly) is: ping this channel to ask for a printer (either we have a free one to give you, or we will add you to the print queue), then when you have one, go to <http://px.nolop.org|px.nolop.org> where the x is the printer number (so <http://p1.nolop.org|p1.nolop.org>, or <http://p2.nolop.org|p2.nolop.org>), and upload you model. From there you can slice it and start the print remotely (full detailed instructions here: <http://nolop.org/3dprint/>)
When it's done we put it outside Nolop on the table and you can come pick it up whenever
